.TH mbm_tmap 1 "18 April 2026" "MB-System 5.0" "MB-System 5.0"
.SH NAME
\fBmbm_tmap\fP \- Macro to convert XYZ point clouds to 3D Tiles and generate a Cesium viewer.

.SH VERSION
Version 5.0

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmbm_tmap\fP \fB-I\fP\fIpointcloud.xyz\fP
[\fB-O\fP\fItiles_dir\fP]
[\fB-P\fP\fIport\fP]
[\fB--serve-only\fP | \fB--no-convert\fP]
[\fB-N\fP]
[\fB-S\fP]
[\fB-W\fP]
[\fB-V\fP]
[\fB-H\fP]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBmbm_tmap\fP is a macro that automates point cloud web visualization setup.
It runs \fBpy3dtiles convert\fP on an input XYZ point cloud file, writes an
\fBindex.html\fP Cesium viewer file into the output tiles directory, and can
optionally start a local HTTP server using \fBpython -m http.server\fP.

By default \fBmbm_tmap\fP performs conversion from XYZ input. If
\fB--serve-only\fP (or \fB--no-convert\fP) is specified, conversion is skipped
and an existing tiles directory is served directly.

This macro is intended for quick local testing and browsing of tiled point cloud
data products.

