.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-I
\fIpointcloud.xyz\fP
.br
Input XYZ point cloud file. This option is required unless
\fB--serve-only\fP or \fB--no-convert\fP is specified.

.TP
.B \-O
\fItiles_dir\fP
.br
Output directory for 3D Tiles and generated \fBindex.html\fP.
Default is \fBtiles\fP.

.TP
.B \-P
\fIport\fP
.br
HTTP server port used when starting \fBpython -m http.server\fP.
Default is \fB8000\fP.

.TP
.B --serve-only, --no-convert
.br
Skip \fBpy3dtiles\fP conversion and serve an existing tiles directory.
In this mode \fB-O\fP should point to an existing tiles directory.
If \fBindex.html\fP already exists it is reused.

.TP
.B \-N
.br
Do not open a browser automatically.

.TP
.B \-S
.br
Do not start a local HTTP server.

.TP
.B \-W
.br
Wait on the server process after starting it. Use Ctrl+C to stop.

.TP
.B \-V
.br
Verbose output.

.TP
.B \-H
.br
Print help message and exit.

.SH EXAMPLES
Convert an XYZ file to tiles and start local server:
.br
\fBmbm_tmap -I cloud.xyz -O tiles -V\fP

Serve an existing tiles directory without reconversion:
.br
\fBmbm_tmap --serve-only -O tiles -P 8081 -W -V\fP

Convert an XYZ file to tiles without starting server:
.br
\fBmbm_tmap -I cloud.xyz -O tiles -S\fP

Start server and keep the macro attached to server lifetime:
.br
\fBmbm_tmap -I cloud.xyz -O tiles -W\fP

